'''Argyll''' is a residential neighbourhood in , , , located on the south side between the two branches of the .  It is bounded by the ravine on the west and north east sides, and by  on the south and south east sides.  On the other side of Mill Creek Ravine are the residential neighbourhoods of  and .  On the other side of Argyll Road is the industrial subdivision of Coronet Addition Industrial.  The Argyll Sports Centre is located in the neighbourhood.
Most residential construction (93%) in the neighbourhood occurred between the end of  and .  Almost all the residences in the neighbourhood are .  The majority (83%) of residences are owner occupied.<ref>[http://censusdocs.edmonton.ca/DD23/FEDERAL%202001/Neighbourhood/ARGYLL.pdf] and [http://censusdocs.edmonton.ca/C05002/MUNICIPAL%202005/Neighbourhood/ARGYLL.pdf]</ref>
Household income for Argyll is close to the average for the City of Edmonton in spite of its close proximity to industrial developments.  This is perhaps the result of recreational facilities and the features of the Mill Creek Ravine.
